## PRINCIPLE 3: MANDATORY ANALYSIS DEPTH LEVELS

Every analysis task MUST declare its depth level:

| Level | Name | Description | When to Use |
|-------|------|-------------|-------------|
| L1 | Surface | Syntax, obvious errors | Typos, lint fixes |
| L2 | Local | Single function/component | Simple bug in one function |
| L3 | Module | Entire module + direct dependencies | Feature bugs |
| L4 | Cross-Module | Multiple modules + their interactions | Integration issues |
| L5 | System | Full system architecture + data flow | Architecture issues, mysterious bugs |

**DEFAULT LEVEL IS L3.** If user reports a bug that has persisted or is mysterious, START at L4.

