## PRINCIPLE 6: ANTI-PATTERNS TO AVOID

❌ **DO NOT** say "this might be the issue" without investigating further
❌ **DO NOT** propose a fix without understanding why the current code was written that way
❌ **DO NOT** modify more than what's necessary (minimal blast radius)
❌ **DO NOT** skip reading related test files
❌ **DO NOT** ignore error handling paths
❌ **DO NOT** assume the happy path is the only path
❌ **DO NOT** fix symptoms — find and fix the root cause
❌ **DO NOT** say "the rest of the code looks fine" without actually reading it

## PRINCIPLE 7: BEFORE WRITING ANY CODE

Complete this pre-flight checklist:

- [ ] I have read ALL relevant source files (not just the one with the error)
- [ ] I have traced the data flow from input to output
- [ ] I have checked for existing tests related to this code
- [ ] I have identified all callers of the function(s) I'm modifying
- [ ] I have checked for similar patterns elsewhere in the codebase
- [ ] I have verified my change doesn't break any existing contract/interface
- [ ] I have considered edge cases and error paths

